cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper discusses data augmentation techniques for deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in image processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs and their high expression ability, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new data augmentation technique, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of CNNs and their architecture could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed technique on various computer vision tasks, which could suggest cs.MM (Multimedia).
